    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 25,
        "summary": "Boast not of false gifts\u2014Give food and drink to your enemy.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "These are also proverbs of Solomon, which the men of Hezekiah king of Judah copied out.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Kgs. 4:32; Prov. 1:1; 10:1.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 23
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 9
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "It is the glory of God to conceal a thing: but the honour of kings is to search out a matter.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 11:33; D&C 5:3.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 33
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The heaven for height, and the earth for depth, and the heart of kings is unsearchable.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Take away the dross from the silver, and there shall come forth a vessel for the finer.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0waste, impurities.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 19
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Take away the wicked from before the king, and his throne shall be established in righteousness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 20:8.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 29:21 (21\u201324).",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Put not forth thyself in the presence of the king, and stand not in the place of great men:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For better it is that it be said unto thee, Come up hither; than that thou shouldest be put lower in the presence of the prince whom thine eyes have seen.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 14:10 (7\u201314).",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Go not forth hastily to strive, lest thou know not what to do in the end thereof, when thy neighbour hath put thee to shame.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 3:30; 17:14.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 30
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Debate thy cause with thy neighbour himself; and discover not a secret to another:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0do not reveal.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Lest he that heareth it put thee to shame, and thine infamy turn not away.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 23
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A word fitly spoken is like apples of gold in pictures of silver.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 15:23; Isa. 50:4.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 6
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "As an earring of gold, and an ornament of fine gold, so is a wise reprover upon an obedient ear.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 1:9.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Chastening.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 2
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "As the cold of snow in the time of harvest, so is a faithful messenger to them that send him: for he refresheth the soul of his masters.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 49
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Whoso boasteth himself of a false gift is like clouds and wind without rain.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Boast.",
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "By long forbearing is a prince persuaded, and a soft tongue breaketh the bone.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Forbear.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 121:41 (41\u201344).",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Hast thou found honey? eat so much as is sufficient for thee, lest thou be filled therewith, and vomit it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 24:13.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Withdraw thy foot from thy neighbour's house; lest he be weary of thee, and so hate thee.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 78
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A man that beareth false witness against his neighbour is a maul, and a sword, and a sharp arrow.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Gossip.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 19:18; Mosiah 13:23.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0scatterer; i.e., some sort of war club.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 64
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 57:4.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 57
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Confidence in an unfaithful man in time of trouble is like a broken tooth, and a foot out of joint.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "As he that taketh away a garment in cold weather, and as vinegar upon nitre, so is he that singeth songs to an heavy heart.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 2
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "If thine enemy be hungry, give him bread to eat; and if he be thirsty, give him water to drink:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 12:44 (43\u201345). TG\u00a0Enemies.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Chr. 28:15.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For thou shalt heap coals of fire upon his head, and the Lord shall reward thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reward.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The north wind driveth away rain: so doth an angry countenance a backbiting tongue.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Backbiting.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "It is better to dwell in the corner of the housetop, than with a brawling woman and in a wide house.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 21:9, 19.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "As cold waters to a thirsty soul, so is good news from a far country.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 2
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 39
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A righteous man falling down before the wicked is as a troubled fountain, and a corrupt spring.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0a trampled spring; i.e., ruined by wading into it. See Ezek. 34:18.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "It is not good to eat much honey: so for men to search their own glory is not glory.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Glory.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that hath no rule over his own spirit is like a city that is broken down, and without walls.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Self-Mastery.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 20
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 63
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}